  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ gas 4, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium to high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>chicken thighs </strong>dry with kitchen paper and season them generously on both sides with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then add to the pan, skin-side down, and cook for 4-5 min or until the skin is golden brown</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong> into<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>wedges</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Pick your <strong>basil leaves</strong> from the <strong>stalks </strong>(you'll be using both)</p><p>Cut your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and slice into long strips</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1671.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
